The patient dose should be measured by a suitable radioactivity calibration system immediately prior to administration of the dose.
Parenteral drug products should be inspected visually for particulate matter and discoloration prior to administration whenever solution and container permit. The solution to be administered as the patient dose should be clear and contain no particulate matter. Do not use an eluate of the TECHNELITEÂ®, Technetium Tc 99m Generator later than one (1) working day after elution (12 hours).
